  "text": "Observe that there exist two ways to edit the centre t. By setting m > 2k we can fix this and obtain a quadratic vertex-kernel for k-BetweennessTour (by adapting techniques from [CITATION_1] ). Nevertheless, this is not enough to obtain a linear vertex kernel. To that aim, we combine Conflict Packing and a sunflower rule on simple conflicts. Proof. Since bca ∈ R is inconsistent with σ, c is not between a and b in σ. Hence we either have b between a and c or a between b and c. Assume w.l.og. that a < σ b < σ c or b < σ a < σ c. The two cases are similar, so assume the former holds. By assumption, the triplet t ∈ R on {b, c, d} is consistent with σ. Consider the three possible cases for t:",
